<concept id="concept_A9A190B372C5450CA53D60431D362143"> 
  <title>Administrators - Getting Started</title> 
  <shortdesc>Learn about being a administrator in the Adobe Marketing Cloud. 
  </shortdesc> 
  <prolog> 
	 <metadata> 
		<keywords> 
		  <keyword>audience services</keyword> 
		</keywords> 
		<othermeta name="solution" content="Marketing Cloud"/> </metadata>
  </prolog> 
  <conbody> 
	 <section id="section_9B9190FB3BDD41B7898EB456A00DC954"> 
		<title>Getting Started Tasks</title> 
		<table id="table_6CC0D1DFA87D4D2B86C246BEEEE1A4C6"> 
		  <tgroup cols="4"> 
			 <colspec colnum="1" colname="col1" colwidth="1.00*"/> 
			 <colspec colname="col002" colnum="2" colwidth="1.19*"/> 
			 <colspec colname="col02" colnum="3" colwidth="1.77*"/> 
			 <colspec colnum="4" colname="col2" colwidth="2.32*"/> 
			 <thead> 
				<row> 
				  <entry colname="col1">Step 
				  </entry> 
				  <entry colname="col002">Who Performs 
				  </entry> 
				  <entry colname="col02">Where 
				  </entry> 
				  <entry colname="col2">Why 
				  </entry> 
				</row> 
			 </thead> 
			 <tbody> 
				<row> 
				  <entry colname="col1"> 
					 <p> 
						<image href="graphics/step1_icon.png"
						 id="image_25AB69C832BB470CA3846E4A52ED840D"></image> Complete the Opt-In
						Application. 
					 </p> 
				  </entry> 
				  <entry colname="col002"> 
					 <p>Administrators 
					 </p> 
				  </entry> 
				  <entry colname="col02"> 
					 <p> 
						<xref
						 href="https://adobeformscentral.com/?f=hC4PfUjb5dP-AjBInCC%2ABA" format="https"
						 scope="external">Adobe Marketing Cloud Interface Opt-In Application</xref> 
					 </p> 
				  </entry> 
				  <entry colname="col2"> 
					 <p>Completing the form notifies the Adobe Customer Provisioning
						Team (CPT) to provision your account. Then, the CPT notifies the Account
						Manager you specified on the form. Your Account Manager then contacts you. 
					 </p> 
					 <p>Once enabled as an administrator, you can access the Tools
						page in the 
						<keyword>Marketing Cloud</keyword>, where you can: 
					 </p> 
					 <ul id="ul_D3532A54DE984AFC9508F394FD552E7C"> 
						<li id="li_94EE0B47DB704DBE888EEA6A6358C97B">Create users 
						</li> 
						<li id="li_543456C6FBE5428F9DFA726E3949AEAA">Create groups 
						</li> 
						<li id="li_DED4EFF844984034B4DDB31613E3AFB9">Invite users to
						  the Marketing Cloud 
						</li> 
					 </ul> 
				  </entry> 
				</row> 
				<row> 
				  <entry colname="col1"> 
					 <p> 
						<image href="graphics/step2_icon.png"
						 id="image_57CD0E4918EF4522AB8422B377B7F694"></image> Create one or more groups.
						
					 </p> 
				  </entry> 
				  <entry colname="col002"> 
					 <p>Administrators 
					 </p> 
				  </entry> 
				  <entry colname="col02"> 
					 <p> 
						<menucascade> 
						  <uicontrol>Tools</uicontrol> 
						  <uicontrol>Group Management</uicontrol> 
						</menucascade> 
					 </p> 
				  </entry> 
				  <entry colname="col2"> 
					 <p>A Group is a container of users. You add users to a group,
						then enable solution access at the group level. 
					 </p> 
				  </entry> 
				</row> 
				<row> 
				  <entry colname="col1"> 
					 <p> 
						<image href="graphics/step3_icon.png"
						 id="image_078728688BEB48DFAC01169F7E534D7B"></image> Add (invite) users to the
						Marketing Cloud organization. 
					 </p> 
				  </entry> 
				  <entry colname="col002"> 
					 <p>Administrators 
					 </p> 
				  </entry> 
				  <entry colname="col02"> 
					 <p> 
						<menucascade> 
						  <uicontrol>Tools</uicontrol> 
						  <uicontrol>User Management</uicontrol> 
						</menucascade> 
					 </p> 
					 <p>You can also perform this step on the 
						<wintitle>Edit Group</wintitle> page, under 
						<wintitle>Solution Access</wintitle>. 
					 </p> 
				  </entry> 
				  <entry colname="col2"> 
					 <p>When you invite a user to the Marketing Cloud organization,
						you specify their email addresses and can associate them with a group. 
					 </p> 
					 <p>Adobe sends the users an email invitation. They must confirm
						their email address by clicking a link in the email, which registers the
						account. (See step 4.) 
					 </p> 
					 <note>If the new user does not yet exist in your solution
						(<keyword>Analytics</keyword>, 
						<keyword>Social</keyword>, or 
						<keyword>Target</keyword>), Adobe recommends the following
						workflow to add the user: 
					 </note> 
					 <ol id="ol_683CE5D1575C42D48E931841D11566D5"> 
						<li id="li_BE35C3E1ABE44166B5DFA2CB233498A1">Add the user as
						  you typically do. (For example, in 
						  <keyword>Analytics</keyword>, use 
						  <uicontrol>Admin Tools</uicontrol> &gt; 
						  <uicontrol>User Management</uicontrol>.) 
						</li> 
						<li id="li_94CFECE2C1714B088072F2F85831DA51">Instruct the
						  user log in to the solution, then click 
						  <uicontrol>Join Marketing Cloud</uicontrol>, and follow the
						  steps to link accounts. 
						</li> 
					 </ol> 
					 <p>See 
						<xref
						 href="access.xml#concept_04341546E8B44CDF833F9DDF351A50B9" format="dita"
						 scope="local"><?xm-replace_text Getting Access to the Marketing Cloud?></xref>
						for more information. 
					 </p> 
				  </entry> 
				</row> 
				<row> 
				  <entry colname="col1"> 
					 <p> 
						<image href="graphics/step4_icon.png"
						 id="image_B3A0B7EB78DE40E198E98E3D7B784C72"></image> Link solution accounts.
						(<xref
						href="link_accounts.xml#concept_DFCB29A3B4834FC59AA29E0BBA301584" format="dita"
						scope="local">Join Marketing Cloud)</xref> 
					 </p> 
				  </entry> 
				  <entry colname="col002"> 
					 <p>Users 
					 </p> 
				  </entry> 
				  <entry colname="col02"> 
					 <p>In solutions (<keyword>Analytics</keyword>, 
						<keyword>Social</keyword>, etc.) or In the 
						<keyword>Marketing Cloud</keyword>. 
					 </p> 
				  </entry> 
				  <entry colname="col2"> 
					 <p>Linking accounts connects a user's Adobe ID (Marketing Cloud
						login) to the user's solution credentials. After users sign in to 
						<filepath><term>&lt;your
							 company&gt;</term>.marketing.adobe.com</filepath>, they are automatically
						signed in to the solution. 
					 </p> 
					 <p>See 
						<xref
						 href="access.xml#concept_04341546E8B44CDF833F9DDF351A50B9" format="dita"
						 scope="local"><?xm-replace_text Getting Access to the Marketing Cloud?></xref>
						for more information. 
					 </p> 
				  </entry> 
				</row> 
				<row> 
				  <entry colname="col1"> 
					 <p> 
						<image href="graphics/step5_icon.png"
						 id="image_49AB4D5F2E0C46AD9CA8DA50FEA9AD06"></image> (Optional) Implement the
						Marketing Cloud Visitor ID Service 
					 </p> 
				  </entry> 
				  <entry colname="col002"> 
					 <p>Administrators 
					 </p> 
				  </entry> 
				  <entry colname="col02"> 
				  </entry> 
				  <entry colname="col2">See 
					 <xref
					  href="audiences_getstarted.xml#concept_B40C2CD97D7242E8A129D73D08DE507D"
					  format="dita" scope="local"><?xm-replace_text Implementing the Marketing Cloud ID?></xref>
					 
				  </entry> 
				</row> 
			 </tbody> 
		  </tgroup> 
		</table> 
		<p>See 
		  <xref href="faq.xml#concept_13219B4E51784577B6FF78AAA203DE91"
			format="dita" scope="local"><?xm-replace_text Marketing Cloud FAQ?></xref> for
		  questions and answers about the 
		  <keyword>Marketing Cloud</keyword>. 
		</p> 
	 </section> 
